  <slide>
    <title>One-sided limits</title>
    <p>
      For <m>f(x) = \begin{cases}4\cos(x), \amp x\lt 0\\2, \amp x=0\\ 2-3x^2, \amp x\gt 0\end{cases}</m>,
      evaluate
      <me>
        \lim_{x\to 0^-}f(x)
      </me>
      and
      <me>
        \lim_{x\to 0^+}f(x)
      </me>.      
    </p>

    <p>
      Reminder: <m>x\to 0^-</m> means <m>x\lt 0</m> and <m>x\to 0</m>. <m>x\to 0^+</m> means <m>x\gt 0</m> and <m>x\to 0</m>.
    </p>
  </slide>

